Author: Regnar#6164
Content: How long are atomic swap orders live for? and what happens when I close BarterDEX after placing an order (fulfilled or not)?

Author: NNoperator#3835
Content: they time out in four hours

Author: Regnar#6164
Content: Is it an arbitrary time out?

Author: cipi#4502
Content: swaps can only be done when BarterDEX is running, if you stop it, no swaps

Author: Regnar#6164
Content: is there any resources on that aspect in particular I can read up on?

Author: Regnar#6164
Content: to understand why swaps can't happen when its off (I assume it has something to do with private keys sending the payments etc) but why the 4 hours?

Author: cipi#4502
Content: swaps can't happen when it's off because BarterDEX can't do transactions when it's off... if you read how atomic swaps work (eg in the whitepaper), it should become clear why it can't work

Author: cipi#4502
Content: if you place orders in orderbook, eg with autoprice and turn off BarterDEX, this entries will disappear after some time, but it is not that important, since swaps woul not happen anyway, it is just to clear the orderbooks of offers that would not work

Author: cipi#4502
Content: this should happen much faster then 4 hours, but i don't know what the time is

Content: Sent you a PM @cipi  Thanks for the help
